            <ul class="- topic/ul " id="ul_bkv_s44_scb" xtrc="ul:1;27:37" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/kheat/Documents/GitHub/New%20folder/LearningDITA/en-us/Learning_and_training_specialization/topics/where_do_you_use_the_l_t_specialization_.dita">
                <li class="- topic/li " xtrc="li:1;28:21" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/kheat/Documents/GitHub/New%20folder/LearningDITA/en-us/Learning_and_training_specialization/topics/where_do_you_use_the_l_t_specialization_.dita">Developing content for instructor-led training. You can use the Learning &amp;
                    Training specialization to create the slides used for the presentation as well
                    the printed materials handed out to students, including: course outlines,
                    workbooks, review materials, and pre- and post-assessments. </li>
                <li class="- topic/li " xtrc="li:2;32:21" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/kheat/Documents/GitHub/New%20folder/LearningDITA/en-us/Learning_and_training_specialization/topics/where_do_you_use_the_l_t_specialization_.dita">Developing content for web or learning management system (LMS) delivery. Just as
                    Scriptorium does for LearningDITA, the Learning &amp; Training specialization
                    allows you to prepare and organize learning content and assessments. </li>
                <li class="- topic/li " xtrc="li:3;35:21" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/kheat/Documents/GitHub/New%20folder/LearningDITA/en-us/Learning_and_training_specialization/topics/where_do_you_use_the_l_t_specialization_.dita">If both the training and documentation teams use DITA, both can develop and
                    share content between the groups. While actual presentation and discussion of
                    materials might take different forms, both groups can share common blocks of
                    text, images, tables of data, and the like through DITA warehouse topics. </li>
            </ul>
